Question 1

dat <- cbind(logR$BAC, logR$JPM)
df_seq <- seq(2.5, 5, 0.01)
n_vals <- length(df_seq)
loglik_vals <- rep(0, n_vals)
for (i in 1:n_vals) {
  fit <- cov.trob(dat, nu = df_seq[i], cor = TRUE)
  mu <- as.vector(fit$center)
  sigma <- matrix(fit$cov, nrow = 2)
  loglik_vals[i] <- sum(log(dmt(dat, mean = mu, S = sigma, df = df_seq[i])))
}
max_idx <- which.max(loglik_vals)
mle_nu <- df_seq[max_idx]
cutoff <- max(loglik_vals) - 0.5 * qchisq(0.95, df = 1)
ci_indices <- which(loglik_vals >= cutoff)
ci_lower <- df_seq[min(ci_indices)]
ci_upper <- df_seq[max(ci_indices)]

plot(df_seq, loglik_vals, type = "l", lwd = 2,
     xlab = "Degrees of Freedom ()",
     ylab = "Profile Log-Likelihood",
     main = "Profile Log-Likelihood for ")
abline(v = mle_nu, col = "blue", lty = 2)
abline(v = c(ci_lower, ci_upper), col = "red", lty = 2)
legend("topright", legend = c("MLE", "95% CI"), col = c("blue", "red"), lty = 2)

bestfit <- cov.trob(dat, nu = mle_nu, cor = TRUE)
best_mu <- bestfit$center
best_cor <- bestfit$cor

mle_nu

c(ci_lower, ci_upper)
## [1] 2.77 3.67
best_mu
## [1] 0.0002786507 0.0007689776

Question 6

u1 <- u2 <- seq(0.01, 0.99, length = 50)
grid <- expand.grid(u1 = u1, u2 = u2)

rho_t <- coef(fit_tcop)[1]
df_t <- round(coef(fit_tcop)[2])
t_cop_fit <- tCopula(param = rho_t, dim = 2, df = df_t, df.fixed = TRUE)
cdf_t <- matrix(pCopula(as.matrix(grid), t_cop_fit), nrow = 50)

rho_norm <- coef(fit_norm)
norm_cop_fit <- normalCopula(param = rho_norm, dim = 2)
cdf_norm <- matrix(pCopula(as.matrix(grid), norm_cop_fit), nrow = 50)

alpha_clayton <- coef(fit_clayton)
clayton_cop_fit <- claytonCopula(param = alpha_clayton, dim = 2)
cdf_clayton <- matrix(pCopula(as.matrix(grid), clayton_cop_fit), nrow = 50)

alpha_joe <- coef(fit_joe)
joe_cop_fit <- joeCopula(param = alpha_joe, dim = 2)
cdf_joe <- matrix(pCopula(as.matrix(grid), joe_cop_fit), nrow = 50)

par(mfrow = c(2, 2))
contour(u1, u2, cdf_t, main = "t Copula (CDF)")
contour(u1, u2, cdf_norm, main = "Normal Copula (CDF)")
contour(u1, u2, cdf_clayton, main = "Clayton Copula (CDF)")
contour(u1, u2, cdf_joe, main = "Joe Copula (CDF)")
